playbookOutput.executionSummary:
Customer: "I just had a baby, and I'd like to add her to my insurance plan. How can I do that?"

Agent: "Congratulations on your new addition! To add your baby to your plan, you'll need to complete a 'Change of Status' form. This is time-sensitive, so it's important to submit the request within 30 days of birth."

Customer: "Where can I find this form?"

Agent: "You can download it from our website or I can email it to you directly. Once completed, you can email it back or mail it to the address provided on the form."

Customer: "What information will I need to provide?"

Agent: "You'll need your baby's birth date, full name, and social security number if available. If you haven't received the social security number yet, you can add it to your plan later."

displayName: Inquiry About Adding Family Members to Existing Coverage
